      "id": 17,
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Host Metrics Setup\n\nThe **HOST RESOURCES** section shows metrics from the Docker stats perspective (physical machine) vs the cluster-internal metrics.\n\n### Current Status\n\n| Metric | Docker Stats | Cluster Metrics |\n|--------|--------------|----------------|\n| **CPU** | Run `docker stats minikube` on host | Node CPU Utilization % above |\n| **Memory** | Run `docker stats minikube` on host | Node Memory Utilization % above |\n\n### To Enable Host Metrics:\n\n1. **Run on your host machine** (where minikube runs):\n\n```bash\n# Create metrics directory\nmkdir -p /tmp/node_exporter_textfile\n\n# Create collection script\ncat > /tmp/docker-stats.sh <<'EOF'\n#!/bin/bash\nSTATS=$(docker stats minikube --no-stream --format \"{{.CPUPerc}},{{.MemUsage}},{{.MemPerc}}\")\nCPU=$(echo \"$STATS\" | cut -d',' -f1 | sed 's/%//')\nMEM_FULL=$(echo \"$STATS\" | cut -d',' -f2)\nMEM_USAGE=$(echo \"$MEM_FULL\" | grep -oP '^\\d[\\d.]*')\nMEM_UNIT=$(echo \"$MEM_FULL\" | grep -oP '\\d[\\d.]*\\s*\\K[MG]iB' | head -1)\nMEM_PERCENT=$(echo \"$STATS\" | cut -d',' -f3 | sed 's/%//')\nif [ \"$MEM_UNIT\" = \"GiB\" ]; then\n  MEM_BYTES=$(echo \"$MEM_USAGE * 1024 * 1024 * 1024\" | bc | cut -d'.' -f1)\nelse\n  MEM_BYTES=$(echo \"$MEM_USAGE * 1024 * 1024\" | bc | cut -d'.' -f1)\nfi\ncat > /tmp/node_exporter_textfile/docker_stats.prom <<PROM\n# HELP docker_cpu_percent CPU from host\n# TYPE docker_cpu_percent gauge\ndocker_cpu_percent{container=\"minikube\"} $CPU\n# HELP docker_memory_bytes Memory from host\n# TYPE docker_memory_bytes gauge\ndocker_memory_bytes{container=\"minikube\"} $MEM_BYTES\n# HELP docker_memory_percent Memory percent from host\n# TYPE docker_memory_percent gauge\ndocker_memory_percent{container=\"minikube\"} $MEM_PERCENT\nPROM\nEOF\nchmod +x /tmp/docker-stats.sh\n\n# Add to cron (runs every minute)\n(crontab -l 2>/dev/null | grep -v docker-stats; echo \"*/1 * * * * /tmp/docker-stats.sh\") | crontab -\n```\n\n2. **The metrics will appear in this section** after:\n   - Node-exporter reads the textfile collector\n   - Prometheus scrapes the metrics\n   - Grafana refreshes the dashboard\n\n### Understanding the Difference\n\n- **Host Metrics (Docker)**: What minikube container uses on your physical machine\n- **Cluster Metrics (Node-exporter)**: What workloads use inside the minikube VM\n- **The difference** is overhead from VM emulation and system services"
      },
